{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"smoky-flare-slug","description":"# Add CI checks as a second code-gate vote (Verified); require BOTH LLM-Review and CI to pass\n\n## Context\nThe v1 code gate (epics d251-05e1-eb55-43b2 infra and b744-4fb9-2d05-4b49 code-review) uses a SINGLE deterministic vote: the Gerrit `LLM-Review` label, cast by the deterministic pass-3 blocker on thresholds. The intended end state is a gate that requires BOTH (a) LLM review AND (b) CI checks (build / test / lint / format) to pass. CI integration needs more design work (which runner, which checks, how it votes the Gerrit `Verified` label, event wiring, re-run / flaky-test policy), so it is deferred to this follow-on epic rather than bundled into v1.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- A second, independent gate vote — the Gerrit `Verified` label — is cast by a CI system on every change.\n- The submit requirement requires BOTH votes: `label:LLM-Review=MAX AND label:Verified=MAX AND -has:unresolved`.\n- A change cannot submit unless LLM review passes AND CI passes; the two are independent gate votes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Design the CI integration: select the runner (e.g. a lightweight Gerrit `stream-events` listener bot that runs the project's checks, Jenkins + Gerrit Trigger, or Zuul) and the check set (build, test, lint, format); define what `Verified` +1 / -1 means.\n- [ ] Add a `Verified` label to the Gerrit rebar project; the CI service account votes it via REST on `patchset-created`.\n- [ ] Update the submit requirement from `label:LLM-Review=MAX AND -has:unresolved` to `label:LLM-Review=MAX AND label:Verified=MAX AND -has:unresolved` (both votes required to submit).\n- [ ] `copyCondition` / re-run policy for `Verified` across trivial rebases (carry vs re-run), consistent with the LLM-Review vote-carry.\n- [ ] CI failure blocks submit; the gate now requires LLM review AND CI independently.\n- [ ] Design notes: cost / latency budget, flaky-test handling, and whether CI runs as a deterministic pre-pass that ALSO feeds the review overlays' scanner-as-ground-truth pattern.\n\n## Out of scope\n- The `LLM-Review` vote itself (v1; epics d251 / b744).","id":"1fa8-9db4-7c1c-48f3","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["gerrit","ci","gate","follow-on"],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Add CI checks as a second gate vote (Verified); require both LLM-Review and CI to pass"},"env_id":"a7f6c5e0-d538-4904-841a-a3fd102c21d7","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782010054104163467,"uuid":"97f49161-8a14-443b-bd56-d620dcffde50"}